02:54.249 --> 03:16.257
and that may have prompted A&M, I don't know, to 
proceed accordingly as a mechanism for deciding

02:54.249 --> 03:16.257
upon its future. But nonetheless, it was a 
fantastic experience for all parties, I believe.

03:26.830 --> 03:29.794
It was, I think, fast moving. It

03:30.715 --> 03:40.168
addressed the questions that were relevant to the 
university. What kind of university do we expect

03:42.325 --> 03:48.795
to have on our centennial anniversary? What kind 
of student body do we want to have? What kind of

03:53.602 --> 03:55.685
programs and curricula? Where should our 
strengths be? Questions of that magnitude, and it

04:00.552 --> 04:06.621
was well done. Concurrent with the Century 
Council study, was one done by the faculty

04:11.165 --> 04:17.470
called the Aspiration Study. And it too, it in fact 
was more specific in its content than was the

04:18.311 --> 04:28.860
Century Council Study. The Century Council Study 
was in some ways pretty highly generalized in its

04:28.880 --> 04:40.750
recommendations. Whereas the aspiration study 
was far more to the point and more specific. And I

04:48.262 --> 04:58.975
think a blend of the two helped chart the course for 
the university in the years to come.

